<h1>TGS Flow Pilot Test PRD</h1>

<p><strong>Purpose:</strong> This document is intentionally minimal so that the backlog generation workflow produces exactly one Epic and one Story during the Sprint 1 validation test.</p>

<h2>Problem</h2>
<p>Engineering teams often forget to update Jira when work begins in GitHub. This results in inaccurate reporting of work in progress and creates additional manual effort for engineers and managers.</p>

<h2>Goal</h2>
<p>Validate that TGS Flow can generate Jira backlog items from a simple planning artifact.</p>

<h2>Scope</h2>
<ul>
<li>Generate a single Epic</li>
<li>Generate one Story under that Epic</li>
<li>Confirm the Story can be assigned and updated through GitHub activity</li>
</ul>

<h2>Epic Definition</h2>

<p><strong>Epic Title</strong></p>

<pre>[TGS TEST] GitHub Activity Sync Validation</pre>

<p><strong>Epic Description</strong></p>

<p>This Epic validates that GitHub commits can automatically update Jira tickets through the TGS Flow workflow.</p>

<h2>Story Definition</h2>

<p><strong>Story Title</strong></p>

<pre>[TGS TEST] Validate GitHub commit updates Jira ticket</pre>

<p><strong>Story Description</strong></p>

<p>An engineer will create a commit referencing the Jira issue key and verify that the commit appears in the Jira activity stream.</p>

<h2>Acceptance Criteria</h2>

<ul>
<li>A Jira Epic is created from this document</li>
<li>A Jira Story is generated under the Epic</li>
<li>The Story can be assigned to an engineer</li>
<li>A GitHub commit referencing the Story appears in Jira</li>
<li>The Story shows GitHub activity after the commit</li>
</ul>

<h2>Test Steps</h2>

<ol>
<li>Run the backlog generation command using this document</li>
<li>Confirm one Epic and one Story are created</li>
<li>Assign the Story to an engineer</li>
<li>Create a GitHub commit referencing the Jira issue key</li>
<li>Confirm the commit appears in the Jira issue activity</li>
</ol>

<h2>Cleanup</h2>

<p>After validation, notify the pilot admins in Slack so the test Epic and Story can be removed.</p>

